                    </div>
                    <span>Way too cliche' and fluffy. Typical bad "self help" book that give the truly valuable books a bad name. Full of scenairos like "she went on to become a successful actress" kinda crap that never say who the person was, or any proof this person ever existed to begin with. You wont feel any smarter reading this one, and will miss your $10 or what ever you paid for it.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Stopping unwanted behaviors</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>3</span>
                      /
                      <span>10</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-07-08</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>A book that explains the power of negative thinking? By taking the self assesment tests in the first section, this book helped to re-shape my life. I have not always been an optimist in my thoughts, this book was written for people like me, realists. I enjoyed the chapter on limiting sub-optimal behaviors the most. Another similar book I would recommend reading is Rat Race Relaxer: Your Potential & The Maze of Life by JoAnna Carey which is set up as a week-by-week action plan for getting more out of life.</span>
                  
              
